e. ingenti consensu: according to tradition Tarquin was the first

Roman to canvass actively in seck- ing office. As king he increased his following in the senate by enlarging that body: he waged suc- cessful war with the Latina. gave magnificent public games. estab- lished the Circus Maximus, and founded the Ludi Romani. A stone wall about the city was started. also the foundation work for the Capitoline temple: sewers were opened to drain the lowest districts of the Forum site. With an in· creased cavalry. Tarquin defeats the Sabines and their town Collatia is surrendered.
